Create a Data Action in Data Cloud

To a target based on a data model object (DMO) or calculated insight to trigger an automation or data integration, create a data action to send an alert or an event. The supported targets are Salesforce Platform Event, Webhook, and Marketing Cloud Engagement. Use a data action to focus on near real-time events and insights at different levels\. For example, at the channel, product, account, service, or individual level. For instance, if a customer visits a troubleshooting page before calling Support, a data action lets Support know to skip unnecessary troubleshooting steps.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create a data action:	Data-Aware Specialists, Architects, and Data Engineers
In Data Cloud, go to the Data Actions tab, and click New.
Select the data action target, and click Next.
Select a data space.
Select either a data model object or calculated insight object type.
From Primary Object, select an object, and then click Next.
If a DMO is mapped to an external data lake object, such as Amazon Redshift, Google BigQuery, or Snowflake, it isn’t available as a primary object.
NOTE Any data lake objects (DLOs) mapped to a DMO that is used as the primary object in a data action must have their primary key field mapped to that DMO.
(Optional) To enrich your data action, select a related object.
A DMO or a data graph mapped to an external data lake object is available as a related object. If you’re creating a data action for a Marketing Cloud Engagement data action target, select a subscriber key value. A subscriber key is the unique identifier of a message recipient in Engagement and determines the email address to use for communication. If a subscriber key doesn’t exist in Engagement, you can’t send a data action event to an Engagement data action target.
Enrich your data action with a data graph.
From Related Object, select the data graph.
Select the related object lookup path where the data is available.
For an Engagement data action target, configure the data extension in Engagement to store the data action payload. See Configure a Data Extension to Store a Data Action Payload.
If you’re using a DMO as a related object, you can add up to 10 related attributes to your data action.
If you select a data graph, you can’t select individual attributes. Instead, the entire payload is sent to the data action target.
Select an event rule and an action rule.
Use the event rule to create an action based on record changes. The action rule evaluates your data action. You can include OR and AND conditions in the action rule.
To add more conditions, click Add Condition.
Select the object, attribute, and operator, and enter a value that can trigger the data action.
Select when to trigger the data action for the record updated event rule.
The Trigger Data Action for Updated Records option is available only if you select the Record Updated event rule. If any action rule condition uses a change operator such as Has Increased or Is Changed, you can’t change the Trigger Data Action for Updated Records setting. To change this setting, remove all change operators from the conditions.
Click Next.
Enter the action name.
The Action API Name field is auto-filled.
Click Save and Publish.

You can view your data action on the record home page. Data actions created by integration users, such as a Copy Fields enrichment, Salesforce CRM enrichment, or Data Cloud-triggered flow using Flow Builder, are read only. You can’t delete, disable, or edit these data actions.

Supported Operators for Event and Action Rule Conditions
To trigger a data action, you can select one or more event rules based on the record actions and specify when to publish data using OR and AND conditions.
